name: AEBuildErrorCode
desc: Represents syntax errors found by an “AEBuild” routine.

items.name: var aeBuildSyntaxNoErr: Int
items.desc: No error.

items.name: var aeBuildSyntaxBadToken: Int
items.desc: An illegal character was specified.

items.name: var aeBuildSyntaxBadEOF: Int
items.desc: An unexpected end of format string was encountered.

items.name: var aeBuildSyntaxNoEOF: Int
items.desc: There were unexpected characters beyond the end of the format string.

items.name: var aeBuildSyntaxBadNegative: Int
items.desc: A minus sign “-” was not followed by digits.

items.name: var aeBuildSyntaxMissingQuote: Int
items.desc: A string was not terminated by a closing quotation mark.

items.name: var aeBuildSyntaxBadHex: Int
items.desc: A hex string contained characters other than hexadecimal digits.

items.name: var aeBuildSyntaxOddHex: Int
items.desc: A hex string contained an odd number of digits.

items.name: var aeBuildSyntaxNoCloseHex: Int
items.desc: A hex string was missing a “$” or “»” character.

items.name: var aeBuildSyntaxUncoercedHex: Int
items.desc: A hex string must be coerced to a type.

items.name: var aeBuildSyntaxNoCloseString: Int
items.desc: A string was missing a closing quote.

items.name: var aeBuildSyntaxBadDesc: Int
items.desc: An illegal descriptor was specified.

items.name: var aeBuildSyntaxBadData: Int
items.desc: Bad data was found inside a variable argument list.

items.name: var aeBuildSyntaxNoCloseParen: Int
items.desc: A data value was missing a closing parenthesis.

items.name: var aeBuildSyntaxNoCloseBracket: Int
items.desc: A comma or closing bracket “]” was expected.

items.name: var aeBuildSyntaxNoCloseBrace: Int
items.desc: A comma or closing brace “}” was expected.

items.name: var aeBuildSyntaxNoKey: Int
items.desc: A keyword was missing from a descriptor.

items.name: var aeBuildSyntaxNoColon: Int
items.desc: In a descriptor, one of the keywords was not followed by a colon.

items.name: var aeBuildSyntaxCoercedList: Int
items.desc: Cannot coerce a list.

items.name: var aeBuildSyntaxUncoercedDoubleAt: Int
items.desc: You must coerce a “@@” substitution.
